  "text": "Proof. As p and p are in the same visibility region, they see the same sequence of points and edges of P , and we have SPT(p) = SPT(p ) (see Figure 2) . Here, SPT(p) is the shortest path tree in P rooted at p. The same argument is valid for q and q . We know that the algorithm of Guibas et al. [CITATION_1] for computing the weak visibility polygon of a segment pq in a polygon P , is based on SPT(p) and SPT(q). Therefore, we can conclude that Guibas's algorithm returns the same result as the WVP(pq) and WVP(p q ).",
